<br>
Simple enough solution. If it's a one time incident, he's learned his lesson now, no big deal, but sure as heck no reason to have him profit from it.  Monks like those gloves a lot.<br>
<br>
Ps: as to loot gained on a raid when it's need before greed... you should have genuine reason to use it.  If you then proceed to gain an upgrade at a later time, it's ok (in my opinion) to sell it.  Basically, there should be some sort of amount of time that has passed... <br>
<br>
Oh, and winning item_x, selling it (because you presumably got something better), then winning item_x again in a need-before-greed scenario, is a Very Bad Thing.<br>
